  "prompt": "What makeup to wear for red dress?",
  "response": "When wearing a red dress, you\u2019ll want to choose makeup that complements the boldness of the outfit while enhancing your natural beauty. Here are some makeup tips to consider:\n\n### Face:\n- **Foundation**: Choose a foundation that matches your skin tone for a flawless base.\n- **Blush**: Opt for a soft peach or neutral blush to avoid clashing with the red dress. If you want more color, a subtle warm pink can work well.\n  \n### Eyes:\n- **Eyeshadow**: Neutral tones like taupe, bronze, or gold complement a red dress nicely. If you want to add a little drama, consider a deep plum, charcoal, or even a hint of shimmer.\n- **Eyeliner**: A classic black or brown eyeliner works well; you could also consider a winged liner for an elegant finish.\n- **Mascara**: Go for a volumizing mascara to make your lashes stand out.\n\n### Lips:\n- **Lip Color**: Depending on the look you want, you can either go for a nude lip to keep the focus on your dress or choose a matching red or a deeper berry color for a striking look. If wearing a bold lip, balance it out with more neutral eye makeup.\n\n### Brows:\n- Keep your eyebrows well-groomed and filled in, emphasizing their natural shape with a brow pencil or powder.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- **Highlight**: Use a subtle highlighter on your cheekbones and brow bones to add some glow.\n- **Setting Spray**: To keep your makeup in place, especially if you're out for an extended period, consider using a setting spray.\n\n### Overall Look:\nAim for balance; if your dress is the focal point, keep the makeup sophisticated but simple. Make sure the makeup enhances your features without competing with the striking color of the dress.",
